title: Honey-Can-Do SHO-02151 Natural Wood Shoe Rack Instruction Video
description: Instruction video for assembling your new Honey-Can-Do SHO-02151 natural wood shoe rack

asset.author: myhoneycando
asset.description: Instruction video for assembling your new Honey-Can-Do SHO-02151 natural wood shoe rack

transcripts: At Honey-Can-Do we are your source for organization, storage and style. We make product assembly easy so that well any honey can do it. To begin remove product contents and group all like parts, locate the supports and notice that they are tapered on top and have grooves near the bottom. Slide the bottom grooves on each support into a corner opening on the lower shelf like this. The grooves hold the bottom shelf in place now attach the top shelf by sliding the corner openings in the shelf onto the tapered ends of each support like this and voila your natural wood shoe rack is ready to showcase all of your fantastic shoe collection while you go shopping for more shoes, happy organizing. At honey-can-do we don't believe you have to go broke to have a beautiful well-organized home and assembly should be easy to do.
